label: European Economic Area (EEA)
definition: Concept representing the latest membership of European Economic Area (EEA)

label: EEA 30 Member States
definition: Concept represent current EEA with 30 Member States that became active from 2020 with exit of UK from EEA31 after Brexit
scopenote: European Economic Area (EEA-31) with 30 Member States post Brexit

label: EEA 31 Member States
definition: Concept representing previous EEA with 31 Member States that was active from 2014 and concluded with the exit of UK in 2022 after Brexit
scopenote: European Economic Area (EEA-31) with 30 Member States pre Brexit

label: European Union (EU)
definition: Concept representing the latest membership of European Union (EU)

label: EU 27 Member States
definition: Concept representing current EU with 27 Member States that became active from 2020 with exit of UK from EEA31 after Brexit
scopenote: European Union (EU-27) with 27 Member States post Brexit. Note that EU27 is also applicable to the 27 Member States in the EU from 2007 to 2013, which is not represented in the LOC extension. If this concept should exist, please submit an issue or proposal

label: EU 28 Member States
definition: Concept representing previous EEA with 31 Member States that was active from 2014 and concluded with the exit of UK in 2022 after Brexit
scopenote: European Union (EU-28) with 28 Member States pre Brexit
